critique: The document is an executive order from President Franklin D. Roosevelt that re-delegates powers between the Secretary of Agriculture and the Administrator of the National Recovery Administration (NRA) concerning the regulation of agricultural industries. It aims to clarify which agency has authority over specific aspects of agricultural commodity handling, processing, and storage. The order seeks to prevent conflicts between the Agricultural Adjustment Act and the National Industrial Recovery Act. There is no information about immigration, civil liberties, or diversity.
